g.aria-label: Distribution of iridescent colours in hummingbird communities results from the interplay between selection for camouflage and communication.
Hugo Gruson, Marianne Elias, Juan L. Parra, Christine Andraud, Serge Berthier, Claire Doutrelant & Doris Gomez
Aim: Test the phenotypic structure (clustering vs oversdispersion) of iridescent colours at the community level on: • 112 hummingbird species • spread accross 189 local assemblages
𝛕st = trait diversity within - trait diversity between
• Phenotypic clustering for hue and hue shift on dorsal patches. ⤷ camouflage? • Phenotypic overdispersion for hue and hue shift on ventral and facial patches. ⤷ communication and mate choice?
